  <description type="morphology">Cauline leaves mostly in 5–8 pairs, blade ± ascending throughout, 0.8–1.2 mm wide. Inflorescences: branches erect to ascending. Flowers: sepals 4.5–7.2 mm, to 8 mm in fruit, ± glabrous; nectaries thickened, molarlike, apically 2-lobed, 1–1.5 mm.</description>
